s"},"created":"2012-11-02T07:28:29.404+0000","updated":"2012-11-02T07:28:29.404+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12613390/comment/13490980","id":"13490980","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandonli","name":"brandonli","key":"brandonli","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Brandon Li","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Sorry of the late reply.\nThe change of method isAbsolute() and isUriPathAbsolute() was added in JIRA HADOOP-4952.\n{noformat}\n \n+  /**\n+   *  True if the path component (i.e. directory) of this URI is absolute.\n+   */\n+  public boolean isUriPathAbsolute() {\n+    int start = hasWindowsDrive(uri.getPath(), true) ? 3 : 0;\n+    return uri.getPath().startsWith(SEPARATOR, start);\n+   }\n+  \n   /** True if the directory of this path is absolute. */\n+  /**\n+   * There is some ambiguity here. An absolute path is a slash\n+   * relative name without a scheme or an authority.\n+   * So either this method was incorrectly named or its\n+   * implementation is incorrect.\n+   */\n   public boolean isAbsolute() {\n-    int start = hasWindowsDrive(uri.getPath(), true) ? 3 : 0;\n-    return uri.getPath().startsWith(SEPARATOR, start);\n+     return isUriPathAbsolute();\n   }\n{noformat}\n\nI guess the change was made to highlight the true method functionality, so the author made a new method isUriPathAbsolute() and added comments to isAbsolute(). However, the isAbsolute() was not removed since it might be out of the scope of that JIRA.\n\n+1 to the new patch.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=brandonli","name":"brandonli","key":"brandonli","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Brandon Li","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2012-11-05T22:15:11.960+0000","updated":"2012-11-05T22:15:11.960+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12613390/comment/13493408","id":"13493408","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sureshms","name":"sureshms","key":"sureshms","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10450","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10450","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10450","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10450"},"displayName":"Suresh Srinivas","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"+1 for the patch.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sureshms","name":"sureshms","key":"sureshms","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10450","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10450","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10450","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10450"},"displayName":"Suresh Srinivas","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2012-11-08T19:15:12.036+0000","updated":"2012-11-08T19:15:12.036+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12613390/comment/13493417","id":"13493417","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/